The paper focuses on improving the disentangling ability of the VAE, which is a popular model in the field of machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. The paper also utilizes a non-parametric latent factor model, the Indian Buffet Process (IBP), which is commonly used in the field of Bayesian non-parametrics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
